{
  "texts": [
    "Studying the impact on collaborative development environments in the field is challenging, as voluntary adoption makes it difficult to disentangle LLM effects from adopter characteristics.",
    "An ideal setting allows researchers to observe an LLM selectively supporting some collaborative projects, but not all projects.",
    "The launch of GitHub Copilot, a widely adopted programming focused LLM in October 2021, provides a rare natural experiment setting that satisfies the requirement of an LLM support for selected projects.",
    "Made available through various integrated development environments in October 2021, GitHub Copilot initially supported certain programming languages like Python and Rust, while omitting others such as R and Haskell.",
    "3 These languages stand as major pillars of the open-source movement with publicly accessible code repositories."
  ]
}